Hey guys,

I'm having a severe crash problem with KSP since the new patch came out. I have been playing Campaign only, so I cannot say for sure it's because of the campaign, but it's annoying nonetheless.

I've already tried the suggestions in the other official thread, without any avail (I do have Windows 7-32 bits, so this could be a problem, or at least a catalyst)

I've noticed a bunch of things:

- After a first launch, and coming back to the spacecenter, there are usually some graphical glitches. The icons of the research tab are missing, and the little + and - icons in the lower right are replaced by weird large blocks. I've also seen 3D objects gone missing.

- After this, the game usually crashes, if not directly then usually when I try to launch again.

Appended are 2 crash logs. I hope the devs can do something with it, or at least explain to me what the precise problem is:

The first is the latest I have. I landed on the mun, grabbed some rocks, and tried to fly away - noticing that I didn't have enough fuel to get in any sort of orbit, I decided to press Space Center to revert to the landing site when it crashed:
